From: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
Subject: [PATCH] nss_init: defer probe until the data-plane glue is armed

With ath11k NSS offload, ath11k.ko and mac80211.ko carry hard symbol
references to qca-nss-drv, so kmodloader loads it at every boot. The
probe boots the NSS firmware, and an unarmed firmware boot takes over
all PPE CPU-port delivery (QID2RID rewrite, measured) and kills host
ethernet RX. Gate the probe on the qca-ppe-nss glue: return
-EPROBE_DEFER until at least one port is armed via fw_mask; the glue
re-attaches the deferred core devices when arming happens.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
--- a/nss_init.c
+++ b/nss_init.c
@@ -37,6 +37,7 @@
 #include "nss_strings.h"
 
 #include <nss_hal.h>
+#include <nss_dp_api_if.h>
 
 #include <linux/module.h>
 #include <linux/platform_device.h>
@@ -116,6 +117,17 @@ extern struct of_device_id nss_dt_ids[];
  */
 static inline int nss_probe(struct platform_device *nss_dev)
 {
+	int ret;
+
+	/*
+	 * Do not boot the NSS firmware until the data-plane glue has at
+	 * least one port armed; an unarmed firmware boot takes over all
+	 * PPE CPU-port delivery and kills host ethernet RX.
+	 */
+	ret = nss_dp_probe_gate(&nss_dev->dev);
+	if (ret)
+		return ret;
+
 	return nss_hal_probe(nss_dev);
 }
 
